    "(112)We will use this approach to organize the numerical study of collective mode spectrum of the broken-symmetry states using time-dependent Hartree-Fock (TDHF), as discussed in Sec.",
    "3.5.The second consideration is that of which symmetries are present to be broken, which can be subtle in the MA-TBG context.",
    "Formally, the only continuous symmetry present in MA-TBG is that of U (1) c charge conservation, since all the remaining symmetries are discrete.",
